.TH "drm_client_rotation" 9 "drm_client_rotation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_client_rotation \- Check the initial rotation value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_client_rotation
.BI "(struct drm_mode_set *modeset "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *rotation "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "modeset" 12
DRM modeset
.IP "rotation" 12
Returned rotation value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks if the primary plane in \fImodeset\fP can hw rotate
to match the rotation needed on its connector.
.SH "NOTE"
Currently only 0 and 180 degrees are supported.
.SH "RETURN"
True if the plane can do the rotation, false otherwise.
